net.sf.appia.protocols.tcpcomplete
Class TcpCompleteSession

java.lang.Object
  net.sf.appia.core.Session
      net.sf.appia.protocols.tcpcomplete.TcpCompleteSession
All Implemented Interfaces:
ManagedSession, InitializableSession
Direct Known Subclasses:
SslCompleteSession
public class TcpCompleteSession
extends Session
implements InitializableSession, ManagedSession

Uses TCP to send/receive events to/from other Appia instances.
TCP connections are established automatically when required and terminated after an inactivity period.

The TCP socket is bound to a local address. If RegisterSocketEvent.localHost is null, HostUtils is used to select one.

Author:
Pedro Vicente, Alexandre Pinto, Nuno Carvalho

Method Detail

init

public void init(SessionProperties params)
Initializes the session using the parameters given in the XML configuration. Possible parameters:
  • dest_timeout time between unused open connections verification. (in milliseconds);
  • max_inactivity number of times that the dest_timeout expires without closing the connection;
  • reader_sotimeout the timeout of the threads that listen on TCP sockets. (in milliseconds);
  • close_inactive_sockets boolean that defines if inactive sockets should be closed or not.
